{
  "texts": [
    "The core objective of tasks related to coreference resolution is the identification of referential relationships within texts.",
    "Pronouns, noun phrases, or alternative expressions are occasionally employed in textual passages to refer to entities introduced earlier.",
    "This task entails the recognition of entities referred to by different segments of the text and is a fundamental research area in the field of NLP.",
    "WiC (Pilehvar and Camacho-Collados, 2019) and CLUEWSC2020 (Xu et al, 2020b) are coreference resolution datasets in the English and Chinese domains, respectively, used to determine whether words in different sentences have the same referential meaning.",
    "WSC (Levesque et al, 2012) does not require comparison but rather demands the specific content to which words refer."
  ]
}